    <string name="login_privacy_read_agreement">I have read and agree to the %1$s, %2$s and %3$s</string>
    <string name="login_privacy_alert_full_content">%1$s is a product provided by Shenzhen Tencent Computer System Co., Ltd. (35th Floor, Tencent Building, Kejizhong 1st Road, Maling Community, Yuehai Street, Nanshan District, Shenzhen). It offers features including interactive live streaming, co-anchoring, karaoke, audio/video chat, and online conferencing. For a quick look at how we collect personal information, see the %2$s.\n\n1. When you sign up with or log in to RT-Cube, we collect your profile information including name, photo, mobile number, and email address. When an error occurs during your use of our services, we collect your package name, system version, and process name, among others. We collect only information essential for you to use our product and services. To learn more about the personal information we collect and how we use it, see %3$s.\n\n2. When you use features such as interactive live streaming, co-anchoring, karaoke, audio/video chat, and online conferencing, we may access your storage space, camera, photos, mic, and network, among others. We will ask for your permission the first time we access these resources. You can deny access or change the access settings.\n\n3. Some of our services are provided by third parties. To learn about the third parties we work with and how we share information with them, see %4$s.\n\n4. You can query, copy, update, or delete your personal information, as well as withdraw your consent for data collection. You can also delete your account. To learn more about your rights over your personal information, see Part 5 of the %5$s.\n\n5. If you have any questions, contact us at Dataprivacy@tencent.com or via other channels provided in the %6$s.\n\n</string>
